column5: All these year end reports and evaluations when there's still fishing to be done.  May not be able to go far or stay out for long, but it's still fishing. Last week the son, Rob D, caught his PS pike while I was catching dink perch.  Was out again, today despite the raw wind to play with pannies.  Had the good fortune of running into a long lost OFNer, JWL. Glad to see he's been doing OK.  There's still 3 1/2 weeks good fishing out there. ( As long as Mamma and the chauffuer let me)
Good stuff Bruce ! Like you say.. still time left for open water. Will be in the boat on Tuesday for sure..
evaluations.  .. It never ends but there's bigger fish to be had......lol
Right on Bruce.... Good to hear you got out for some fun Thanks for sharing Jacques
Looks to me like Rob D caught a wee 'ski!
could be not overly sure tho
It's a pike. Their markings look that way when they're young.  Nice outing.
that little pike still cut my 10 lb braided line when taking the hook out its mouth
Ive got you beaten on the wee pikie.the pike was smaller than the worm,and a pickeral too boot after that,even smaller.Memories are coming back now.
